    "Strongly committed to promote art historical research, he worked closely together with <a href=\"/coremansp\">Paul Coremans</a>, the head of the <em>Central Iconographical Records for National Art and Central Laboratory of Belgian Museums</em> in Brussels (ACL, which became, in 1957, the Royal Institute for the Study and Conservation of Belgium's Artistic Heritage).": [],
    "Together, they founded the <em>National Centre for the Study of the \"Primitifs Flamands\"</em> (1949).": [],
    "It is internationally known for its triple series of publications: the <em>Corpus de la peinture des anciens Pays-Bas m\u00e9ridionaux au quinzi\u00e8me si\u00e8cle</em> (<em>Primitifs Flamands Corpus</em>), the <em>R\u00e9pertoire des peintures flamandes des quinzi\u00e8me et seizi\u00e8me si\u00e8cles,</em> and the <em>Contributions \u00e0 l'\u00e9tude des Primitifs Flamands</em>.": [],
    "In 1953-1958, Lavalleye published a two-volume catalog on fifteenth- and sixteenth-century Flemish and Hispano-Flemish art preserved in Spain: <em>Collections d'Espagne</em> (published in the <em>R\u00e9pertoire</em> series).": [
